Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer position with Grow Therapy. I bring over three years of professional experience in backend engineering, production systems, and AI-powered platforms, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the technical depth and ownership this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and shipped backend services and APIs that translate natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API design, data integrity, and service reliability across a distributed system. To keep these systems production-ready, I architected an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to debug production incidents, track quality, and support data pipelines for analytics. I also optimized system performance through A/B testing and system design improvements, reducing latency by 60% and LLM costs by 50% — demonstrating the kind of iterative, data-driven approach to scalability and reliability that Grow Therapy values. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to backend infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I built a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs, ensuring data integrity and scalability. I also contributed to backend development of an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with a focus on service reliability, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and prevent Lambda timeouts, improving production system stability. Together, these roles have prepared me to own the full lifecycle of backend features — from scoping and implementation through testing, deployment, and iteration — and contribute meaningfully to Grow Therapy's core platform systems.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, technical communication, and cross-functional collaboration — skills that translate directly into the collaborative, product-focused engineering culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training and fine-tuning. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle — from training runs to inference optimization using vLLM and deployment via Hugging Face — ensuring production-grade reliability. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the cross-functional collaboration and communication skills central to working closely with Product, Design, and Data teams. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Grow Therapy's mission.

I have always been passionate about making mental healthcare accessible and affordable and building win-win-win solutions for clients, providers, and partners, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Grow Therapy's mission to get more people into therapy by bridging the gap between therapists and people seeking mental health care. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

